"v.免职；作证 【英】 n. 免职，废黜(to remove from office or a position of power) 【记】 de+pose(放)→放下去 →免职 【同】 参考：position(职位 ); repose(休息，宁静) 【例】 The head of state was deposed by the army. n. 免职; 宣誓作证(通过宣誓证实); 沉淀 = deposit 【记】de下, pose放－放下去－免职 源于: deposit(v 沉淀) 【参】repose(v /n 休息) 【记】de 去掉，否定 + position 职位→去职，免职；deposit 沉淀→向下沉； 【相关】appose(放到旁边)并列,depose(从位置上拿下)免职, dispose(向四周摆放位置)部署,expose 暴露, impose 强加，征税, interpose 提出, oppose 对立，反对, repose 休息，座落, transpose 调换位置 depose (v.)  c.1300, from Old French deposer (12c.), from de- ""down"" (see de-) + poser ""put, place"" (see pose (v.1)). Related: Deposed; deposing."
